,Recommended,246760,30441137,Posted: 10 March,all,Aubrielle,"I can't say enough good things about Legends of Eisenwald.Aterdux has managed to create, for me, the ultimate medieval atmosphere.  It's what the Middle Ages feels like to you when you're a kid and all you know are the stories about knights and castles, before you learn about all the bad things that happened in history.  Eisenwald is a journey across an idealized medieval landscape, to the sounds of a beautiful score, with the sun lighting your way as it wanders across the sky.  Your quests will take you across a green countryside and into castles, towns, churches, and taverns.  You will listen to rumors, hire men-at-arms and healers, and battle brigands in turn-based tactical combat reminiscent of Heroes of Might and Magic.  I've made it sound overly simplistic, but the truth is that it's not a complicated game.  It's a vacation, a trip into a simpler time and place, and there is a beauty and innocence to the atmosphere that few games could hope to capture.Aterdux themselves are a wonderful team, and Alex is the friendliest project lead I've ever met.  He's always taken time out to answer any question I've had and to indulge my curiosity, both as a journalist and an Eisenwald fan.  This is a developer worth supporting, and a pleasant journey you owe it to yourself to experience."
