76561198044619825,Recommended,246760,21170860,"Posted: 12 February, 2016",all,mcmorris23,"This is a fun RPG game with an engaging story and satisfying quests. Well done for an independant developer.The primary difference between LoE and other turn-based-combat games is that you do not get to attack whoever you want in battle. You must attack the closest emeny to you. This allows for less strategy in battle and makes battles more difficult. Thus, it is important that you arrange your ground troops correctly according to their initiative, front row to back row, otherwise an infantry man will get stuck behind another troop and not be able to act until that troop is able to move. In the case of archers, you can attack anyone but the further away they are from the enemy the less damage they inflict.All in all, worth the money."
