asant would you have your mighty lord carry out for you today type of thing. Also the quests themselves can be quite baffling and the log is no help; vague is putting it midly. You simply only have to google the undead graveyard quest to see a litany of baffled seekers; one of which even trolls, and rightly so, one of the developers who decides to post in the thread.I will admit there is something about the game that keeps you playing but after the first chapter i just couldn't face the thought of levelling every sinlge character in my party again, despite figuring out how to use potions out of combat by this stage......there is no tutorial as such; wait there is it just doesnt cover things like potions. Oh yes they game on every new chapter strips you of items.......gold.......party members but you do get to keep your carry over on the final chapter from what im told. Can i skip ahead to that last chapter then so my hours of play don't feel like such a dissapointment every time i complete a chapter......sadly no you can'tThere are older and better games out there that do this better than this title; it had a lot of promise in pre release but sadly it never lived up to that promise."
76561197987838464,Recommended,246760,34804550,Posted: 7 September,all,madrigal,"So far I like this game because you can turn the timer on and turn the speed up so that map travel is not pokey slow.  Or you can turn the timer off so that nobody moves unless you do.  This is a great feature to be able to adjust the game travel speed.  People complaining about it being slow maybe didn't notice this feature.  There's an auto-combat feature to speed up combat, but I haven't used it yet.  The strategy, leveling system, and combat are refreshingly different from HOMM and other similar games so you don't feel like it's just a clone.  Most of the fun is figuring out by oneself how it all works.  The artwork is well-done but not flashy.  The game seems solid, no crashes or interface problems.  It feels a bit low-budget in some ways, but nothing is broken.  There is a nice balance between combat and questing.  I give it 8/10."
